  "text": "The rats in group II ( = 108) were applied arthrotomy under ketamine HCl and xylazine anaesthesia, and a complete layer of cartilage injury was formed in their medial femoral condyles ( Figure 1 ) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . From the right knees of the rats where injury was formed, synovial fluid samples were taken by the same technique on the 15th day. Then, arthrotomy was applied and cartilage tissue samples were taken from their distal medial condyles. These rats were sacrificed after this operation.",
